Ctrl+Shift+Q:Cancel All:‾ 1234:// ======================‾0D‾0A// CANCEL ALL ORDERS
 + DELETE TP ALERTS (CURRENT SYMBOL)‾0D‾0A// Group:
 Global controls & config‾0D‾0A// =================
=====‾0D‾0A// Cancels all working orders for the cu
rrent symbol, then clears TP alerts.‾0D‾0A‾0D‾0A// 
---- Step 1: Focus Primary_OE and cancel all orders
 ----‾0D‾0AFocusWindow Primary_OE;‾0D‾0ACXL ALLSYMB
;‾0D‾0A‾0D‾0A// ---- Step 2: Read montage context -
---‾0D‾0A$M = GetWindowObj("Primary_OE");‾0D‾0Aif (
!IsObj($M)) {‾0D‾0A    // If we can't access Primar
y_OE, we can't safely infer symbol/position‾0D‾0A  
  return;‾0D‾0A}‾0D‾0A‾0D‾0A// Snapshot symbol and 
position after cancels‾0D‾0A$mySym   = $M.Symb;‾0D‾0A
$posNow  = $M.Pos;‾0D‾0A‾0D‾0A// ---- Step 3: Re-ar
m stop if long (optional) ----‾0D‾0Aif ($posNow > 0
 && $useAutoStop == "Yes" && $resetStopOnCancel == 
"Yes") {‾0D‾0A    ExecHotkey("Set Auto Stop");‾0D‾0A
}‾0D‾0A‾0D‾0A// ---- Step 4: Delete TP alerts for t
his symbol ----‾0D‾0A// This matches how the TP Ale
rt Builder names them:‾0D‾0A// "TP " + <factor> + "
R Partial " + <symbol>‾0D‾0A‾0D‾0A$i = 1;‾0D‾0A// i
=1..20  -> factors: 0.5, 1.0, 1.5, ..., 10.0‾0D‾0Aw
hile ($i <= 20) {‾0D‾0A    $f = ($i * 0.5);   // 0.
5, 1, 1.5, 2, ...‾0D‾0A‾0D‾0A    $name = "TP " + $f
 + "R Partial " + $mySym;‾0D‾0A‾0D‾0A    $al = GetA
lertObj($name);‾0D‾0A    if (IsObj($al)) {‾0D‾0A   
     $al.Delete();‾0D‾0A    }‾0D‾0A‾0D‾0A    $i = $
i + 1;‾0D‾0A}‾0D‾0A‾0D‾0Areturn;‾0D‾0A
