‾0D‾0A// ---- Step 7: Build and set take profit tri
gger (optional) ----‾0D‾0A// Only (re)build TP if w
e are NOT already profitable on the existing positi
on.‾0D‾0A// For longs, "profitable" means: BID > av
gBefore on the position that existed‾0D‾0A// before
 this entry. If we're already green, do NOT reset T
P.‾0D‾0Aif ($useTakeProfit == "Yes") {‾0D‾0A‾0D‾0A 
   // If no position beforehand, always set TP (fre
sh trade)‾0D‾0A    if ($posBefore <= 0) {‾0D‾0A    
    ExecHotKey("Set Take Profit");‾0D‾0A    } else 
{‾0D‾0A        // We had a long position before thi
s add. Check profitability.‾0D‾0A        $bidNow = 
BID;‾0D‾0A‾0D‾0A        // If avgBefore is invalid,
 be conservative and allow TP reset‾0D‾0A        if
 ($avgBefore <= 0) {‾0D‾0A            ExecHotKey("S
et Take Profit");‾0D‾0A        } else {‾0D‾0A      
      // Only reset TP if NOT yet profitable (bid <
= avgBefore)‾0D‾0A            if ($bidNow <= $avgBe
fore) {‾0D‾0A                ExecHotKey("Set Take P
rofit");‾0D‾0A            }‾0D‾0A            // els
e: already profitable -> do nothing, keep existing 
TP‾0D‾0A        }‾0D‾0A    }‾0D‾0A}‾0D‾0A‾0D‾0A// -
--- End ----
